<section id="To_remove_Policy_Profiles_from_a_Virtual_Machine" remap="TID_14790">
	<title>Removing Policy Profiles from a Virtual Machine</title>
	<procedure>
		<title>To Remove Policy Profiles from a Virtual Machine</title>
		<step>
			<para>
				Navigate to <menuchoice><guimenu>Infrastructure</guimenu><guisubmenu>Virtual Machines</guisubmenu></menuchoice>, check the virtual machines you want to remove the policy profile from.
			</para>
		</step>
		<step>
			<para>
				Click 
				<inlinemediaobject>
					<imageobject>
						<imagedata fileref="images/1941.png" />
					</imageobject>
				</inlinemediaobject> (<guilabel>Policy</guilabel>), and then click 
				<inlinemediaobject>
					<imageobject>
						<imagedata fileref="images/1952.png" />
					</imageobject>
				</inlinemediaobject>(<guilabel>Manage Policies</guilabel>).
			</para>
		</step>
		<step>
			<para>
				Uncheck the policy profile you need to remove. It turns blue to show that its assignment state has changed.
			</para>
		</step>
		<step>
			<para>
				Click <guibutton>Save</guibutton>.
			</para>
		</step>
	</procedure>
</section>